{
  "texts": [
    "They suggest increasing sample sizes and pre-registering studies.",
    "Furthermore, computer code should be made available (Peng, 2011).",
    "Following these recommendations, researchers are increasingly making their materials and code available, pre-registering their studies, and increasing their sample sizes (Tenney et al., 2021).",
    "However, in an effort to increase sample sizes, researchers are increasingly relying on online data collection, rather than in-person studies, which comes with trade-offs (Baumeister, 2016).",
    "Ullman et al. (2021) and Strait et al. (2020) argue that the difficulty of replicating results in the field of HRI is due to the wide variety of robots used."
  ]
